amy takes the reader on a compelling and accessible journey through compulsory monogamy, polyamory, and polyqueer sex and relationships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aNon-monogamous relationships. 0aQueer theory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479801596.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479895342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479895342/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles